{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.28",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 28 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:1",
      "text": "Silver hath beginnings of its veins, and gold hath a place wherein it is melted.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:2",
      "text": "Iron is taken out of the earth, and stone melted with heat is turned into brass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:3",
      "text": "He hath set a time for darkness, and the end of all things he considereth, the stone also that is in the dark and the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:4",
      "text": "The flood divideth from the people that are on their journey, those whom the food of the needy man hath forgotten, and who cannot be come at.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:5",
      "text": "The land, out of which bread grew in its place, hath been overturned with fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:6",
      "text": "The stones of it are the place of sapphires, and the clods of it are gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:7",
      "text": "The bird hath not known the path, neither hath the eye of the vulture beheld it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:8",
      "text": "The children of the merchants have not trodden it, neither hath the lioness passed by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:9",
      "text": "He hath stretched forth his hand to the flint, he hath overturned mountains from the roots.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:10",
      "text": "In the rocks he hath cut out rivers, and his eye hath seen every precious thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:11",
      "text": "The depths also of rivers he hath searched, and hidden things he hath brought forth to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:12",
      "text": "But where is wisdom to be found, and where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:13",
      "text": "Man knoweth not the price thereof, neither is it found in the land of them that live in delights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:14",
      "text": "The depth saith: It is not in me: and the sea saith: It is not with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:15",
      "text": "The finest gold shall not purchase it, neither shall silver be weighed in exchange for it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:16",
      "text": "It shall not be compared with the dyed colours of India, or with the most precious stone sardonyx, or the sapphire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:17",
      "text": "Gold or crystal cannot equal it, neither shall any vessels of gold be changed for it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:18",
      "text": "High and eminent things shall not be mentioned in comparison of it: but wisdom is drawn out of secret places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:19",
      "text": "The topaz of Ethiopia shall not be equal to it, neither shall it be compared to the cleanest dyeing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:20",
      "text": "Whence then cometh wisdom? and where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:21",
      "text": "It is hid from the eyes of all living, and the fowls of the air know it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:22",
      "text": "Destruction and death have said: With our ears we have heard the fame thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:23",
      "text": "God understandeth the way of it, and he knoweth the place thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:24",
      "text": "For he beholdeth the ends of the world: and looketh on all things that are under heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:25",
      "text": "Who made a weight for the winds, and weighed the waters by measure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:26",
      "text": "When he gave a law for the rain, and a way for the sounding storms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:27",
      "text": "Then he saw it, and declared, and prepared, and searched it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.28.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:28",
      "text": "And he said to man: Behold the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom: and to depart from evil, is understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
